In the DFS function, if the remaining number of highways is 0, return the cost accumulated so far. Iterate through each highway, find the next city, and ensure that it has not been visited already. If a valid next city is found, recursively call the DFS function with the updated cost and remaining highways. Keep track of the maximum cost obtained during each iteration, and return the maximum cost after completing the loop.

